{
  "$description": "Dark-world hue steps (Graphite + Carbon contexts). Ratified 2026-07-13, unchanged from the first eyeball pass (dark world read well immediately). tint sits only ΔL 0.02 above the Graphite panel — chroma carries the separation; verified by eye on both dark themes. tint-ink is same-hue light ink, ≥ Lc 60 on its tint. ring added 2026-07-17 (Phase C adjudication, PIN — eye-tune in the token-gaps round): L 0.74 C 0.12 starting symmetry clears ring Lc ≥ 45 on both dark panels (worst hue magenta at 49.4, computed); world-independent solids measure only Lc 20–43 here, which is why the step exists.",

